## Game modes

### Adaptive training

The main mode automatically adjusts the board configuration and difficulty to the player’s current abilities.

### Timed level mode

A set of 32 predefined challenges completed under time pressure. Progress unlocks new visual elements and card themes.

### Challenge mode

The user can select available board configurations and compare the best and worst results for each variation.

## Gamification

The application includes:

- points awarded after completed games,
- achievements for specific milestones,
- unlockable visual themes,
- an internal shop,
- card, menu and splash-screen personalization,
- rewards designed to increase long-term engagement.

## Reports and rankings

The application stores detailed information about completed sessions, including:

- level,
- board size,
- game mode,
- completion time,
- effectiveness,
- score,
- number and type of mistakes.

The ranking can be filtered by date, card configuration, completion time, score and number of mistakes.

Users can also generate PDF reports containing:

- training history,
- detailed results,
- charts,
- mistake analysis,
- progress information,
- cognitive training recommendations.

